# Embedding Any JavaScript

Inside `{}` you can put any JavaScript expression – something that produces a value.

```jsx
const user = { name: 'Alice', isAdmin: true };
const element = (
  <View>
    <Text>Hello, {user.name.toUpperCase()}!</Text>
    <Text>Admin: {user.isAdmin ? 'Yes' : 'No'}</Text>
    <Text>2 + 2 = {2 + 2}</Text>
  </View>
);
```

⚠️ You **cannot** put statements (like `if`, `for`) inside `{}`. Use ternary operators or move logic outside JSX.

## Ways to Conditionally Render

1. **Ternary operator** (inline)
   ```jsx
   {isLoggedIn ? <Text>Welcome</Text> : <Button title="Login" />}
   ```

2. **Logical &&** (when you only want to render something if true)
   ```jsx
   {unreadCount > 0 && <Text>You have {unreadCount} messages</Text>}
   ```

3. **If statement outside JSX**
   ```jsx
   let greeting;
   if (isLoggedIn) {
     greeting = <Text>Welcome back</Text>;
   } else {
     greeting = <Text>Please sign in</Text>;
   }
   return <View>{greeting}</View>;
   ```

