## What are Fragments?

Sometimes you need to return multiple elements without adding an extra `<View>` to the layout. Use a **Fragment**.

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import { Text } from 'react-native';

export default function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <>
      <Text>Line 1</Text>
      <Text>Line 2</Text>
    </>
  );
}
```

The empty tags `<>...</>` are shorthand for `<React.Fragment>...</React.Fragment>`. Fragments don't create any extra native views – they just group children.
